included.description: This proposed invention utilizes on-screen cues paired with website analytics to notify users that relevant content exists below the fold and requires scrolling.  By providing on-screen cues, the invention provides users greater awareness of material below the fold in the case they do not notice the scrollbar.  This is especially important for mobile browsers without persistent scrollbar.  Utilizing site analytics such as number of clicks for buttons, form fields, or links, or determining usersâ screen-size can assist in determining what is presented on screen to the user then provide more information, assisting users to determine which sections of the site are most important.
included.title: Smarter Srcolling - Site analytics and visual display to prompt users to scroll on webpages

included.description: The current invention will aid the end-user when entering form data on mobile devices by providing a viewing area that displays information about the active field as well as the active field relative to the rest of the form. To elaborate, the display area displays the current fieldâs label, whether or not the field is required, access to help, as well as the fieldâs relative location in the form. In addition, using analytics, the average time to complete the form from the active field, is also displayed. This viewing area is not restricted to mobile users, but could also be displayed on laptops and desktops alike.
included.title: Form Entry Aid for Mobile Devices
